Package algorithms.shortestPaths

Class JohnsonsAllPairs

java.lang.Object
algorithms.shortestPaths.JohnsonsAllPairs
public class JohnsonsAllPairs extends Object
all-pairs shortest path algorithm for sparse graphs. finds shortest paths between every pair of vertices v, v' in the graph. there can be negative edge weights in the input graph, but no negative weight cycles. runtime complexity is O(|V|^2 + |V||E|) which is better than Floyd-Warshall if E is less than V^2. implemented following Cormen, Leiserson, Rivest, and Stein "Introduction to Algorithms".
Author:
nichole

  • Constructor Details

    • JohnsonsAllPairs

      public JohnsonsAllPairs(SimpleLinkedListNode[] graph, gnu.trove.map.TIntIntMap[] weights)
      Parameters:
      graph - directed weighted graph where the main index of the object array is the vertex number, and each vertex has a linked list of outgoing edges connecting to the vertexes held in each linked list node key. Note that all vertexes, including edge vertexes, must be present as an index of the array graph, i.e. all vertexes must have numerical value less than dAG.length.
      weights - the edge weights in format of outer array index being the first vertex and the map within having a key being the 2nd vertex of the edge with value being the edge weight.
